		<tr>
			<td><br><img src=/shared_files/techspeakers_photos/Hamai_Kiyoshi.JPG align=left valign="top">&nbsp;H. Kiyoshi Hamai, Senior Director of Sales & Marketing, brings more than 25 years of experience in consumer product distribution, marketing and sales to Mio Technology.  He is responsible for all retail operations, and oversees the development and marketing of Mio’s North American products. <br><br>
Hamai served as VP of Strategic Business Development and VP of Product Management with Tele Atlas North America until 2004.  While with Tele Atlas Hamai was involved in securing partnerships with Telematics service providers, vehicle navigation firms and GIS companies.<br><br>
Prior to joining Tele Atlas, Hamai was Director of Sales for Purple Moon, a start-up consumer software company, which successfully launched an entirely new category and genre of video games for girls.  Hamai also helped launch Creative Wonders, a joint venture between Electronic Arts and ABC, which created, developed and published children’s educational software products under well-known brands such as Schoolhouse Rock, Sesame Street and Madeleine.<br><br>
Hamai holds a bachelor’s of science degree in mathematics from the University of California, Davis.</td>
		
		
